      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Strengthening border security and enforcing immigration laws is crucial to maintaining national sovereignty and protecting American jobs. A well-constructed argument can highlight the importance of securing the southern border, citing statistics on the significant increase in asylum claims and the resulting strain on public resources. Additionally, a strong case can be made for increasing deportations of undocumented immigrants, as it would send a clear message to would-be migrants and discourage future attempts to cross the border illegally.",
